														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3254643">
									

<p>New person but I have seen people say these things before.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dogs and cats</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>There are already a lot of cat and dog SCPs. I get it, they are cute but you can do a different kind of &quot;pet&quot; SCPs. You can do a ferret, I don't think I have ever seen a ferret SCP.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Scary does not always equal can kill you or make you crazy</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>SCP-3974 can kill you but it is not scary because of that. It turns chocolate and chocolate making into a scary thing. So remember you can make an SCP that makes the reader not sleep without killing someone.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Anart does not have to kill people</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>The story &quot;The Critic&quot; shows that anart should not always be something that kills a person. And as the critic said, &quot;how can we open people's minds if all that our projects do is kill them?&quot; Also look at SCP-1559, it doesn't kill people and it doesn't make them mad but is still good.</p>

							</div>

								
					
