			<div class="content" id="post-content-2831260">
									

<ul>
<li><strong>Catalog Entry</strong>
<ul>
<li>The author takes the format literally and thinks that they are just supposed to write a boring bureaucratic report about how some weird thing is contained. SCP articles only <em>look</em> like this; what they really are is a short story that is told within the restrictions of the format. Yes, this is challenging, and yes, the format itself is often at cross purposes with this goal. <em>This is the point.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Units of Measurement</strong>
<ul>
<li>Use of non-SI units, or obvious conversions from US Customary. This includes firearms: <em>caliber <span style="text-decoration: underline;">inches</span> are not SI and guns are <strong>not</strong> some magical exception to using SI units</em>.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>

