														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2833489">
									

<p>That first one is a big one for me as well: There are very, very few creatures that will kill on sight, especially predators: a mountain lion is more likely to ignore you or go find a quieter place to nap than it is to attack you. They do attack people when you do something to tick them off or they're starving, but most of the time we humans simply are not worth the trouble.</p>
<p>On that point, most of the animals you really have to worry about are herbivores: an alligator will attack if you get close and it's hungry. A hippo will attack because you're looking at its stretch of river.</p>

							</div>

								
					
